ington louisiana during the bus tour she marched with sheehan in  with the women say no to war campaign which was meant to deliver a petition with over  signatures of citizens against the war wright has willingly been arrested while taking part in antiwar demonstrations the first such arrest occurring in front of the white house on september   she has said in interviews that she does not remove the arrest bracelets attached to her wrists upon the processing of her arrest but rather collects them on october   wright interrupted a senate foreign relations committee hearing shouting at secretary of state condoleezza rice stop the war stop the killing wright was uneventfully escorted out of the hearing room wright served as one of five judges at the january  sessions of the international commission of inquiry on crimes against humanity committed by the bush administration she was also one of three recipients of the first annual truthout freedom and democracy awards wright was one of three witnesses called to testify at an article  hearing on behalf of us army lt ehren watada who on june   refused to deploy to iraq with his unit asserting that the war violates both the united states constitution and international law on april   wright was cited along with  other antinuclear activists for trespassing at the nevada test site during a nevada desert experience event protesting against the continued development of nuclear weapons by the united states that evening wright appeared on the oreilly factor to discuss the geneva conventions and how they applied to iran in its taking of  british hostages the discussion grew heated and wright stated that she had served  years in the military during the course of the exchange oreilly questioned wrights patriotism and when she pointed out she had served  years in the military and oreilly had never served at all her microphone was cut off on april   wright attended a hearing of a house foreign affairs subcommittee she was ejected from the hearing room after speaking out of turn in response to comments made by republican congressmember dana rohrabacher on september   wright was arrested and later convicted for disrupting a senate armed services committee hearing at which general david petraeus and ambassador to iraq ryan crocker were testifying wright took part in a september   protest march and diein on the steps of the united states capitol building organized by the answer coalition and iraq veterans against the war ivaw she was arrested for stepping over the wall after several ivaw and veterans for peace members were arrested on october   wright and code pink activist medea benjamin were denied entry to canada because their names appear on an fbi database called the national crime information center due to arrests related to their antiwar activism wright and benjamin were told that if they wish to enter canada in the future they will have to apply for residents permits in regards to the incident a canadian mp olivia chow was alarmed to learn that canadian border police are enforcinig rules that have been determined by the fbi and other usbased agencies in december  wright has recently expressed her dissatisfaction with the current us foreign policy toward palestine in  wright began work as a leading member of the steering committee for the gaza freedom march in august  she was among the signatories of an open letter to german chancellor angela merkel by the group veteran intelligence professionals for sanity in which they urged the chancellor to be suspicious of us intelligence regarding the alleged invasion of russia in eastern ukraine gaza flotillaedit main article gaza flotilla raid on june   wright was interviewed by democracy now she was on the challenger  and observed the israeli soldiers rappeling down from helicopters onto the deck of the turkish ship mavi marmara her own ship was boarded flash bangs were used one of our journalists was hit with something of an electric shock i don’t know that it was a taser  while on tour afterwards she claimed that she had witnessed the murder of nine innocent civilianscitation needed however in an interview with aaron lerner of imra she acknowledged that she did not actually see the clash between the idf soldiers and the armed passengers on board the mavi marmaracitation needed in fact it was dark outside because it was predawn and she was on another ship the challenger which was about  yards away from the marmara wright was one of five activists who offered themselves up for arrest in rep brad shermans office after he made a public statement that any american who provides humanitarian aid to gaza should be prosecuted under the antiterrorism and effective death penalty act of  no arrests were made september th attacks and the  commission reportedit in a  interview on the air america radio network wright described the  commission report on the september  terrorist attacks as totally inadequate adding that she does not understand why the us national intelligence and defense operations completely failed and how the pentagon could be hit on  earlier in  she had signed a letter to congress criticizing the commission report for serious shortcomings and omissions which according to the signatories renders the report flawed and casts doubt on the validity of its recommendations writingsedit in  koa books published dissent voices of conscience coauthored by ann wright and susan dixon subtitled government insiders speak out against the war in iraq the work includes a forward by longtime antiwar activist daniel ellsberg who leaked the topsecret pentagon papers in  quotesedit “refusing to participate in military operations that violate international law  the war of aggression the use of torture the use of illegal weapons and purposeful targeting of innocent civilians will save lt watada his sanity and his soul” see alsoedit biography portal united states army portal first lieutenant ehren watada  former active duty united states army officer who is also against the iraq war referencesedit  nation conversations ret col ann wright on israels raid the nation june   retrieved june     rushworth katherine  october  the truth for to tell syracuse post standard retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   a b c mehren elizabeth  january  shes on activist duty now los angeles times retrieved  november    tehranian majid clements kevin p eds  america and the world the double bind london transaction publishers p  isbn    hulburt dory  may  another side to war taos news retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   felice william f  how do i save my honor war moral integrity and principled resignation lanham maryland rowman  littlefield publishers inc pp – isbn    benjamin medea evans jodie eds  stop the next war now effective responses to violence and terrorism maui hawaii inner ocean publishing inc pp – isbn    deserter antiwar activists testify on behalf of soldier colorado springs gazette  august  retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   peace activist cindy sheehan  others arrested outside us mission to the un logansport pharos tribune  march  retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   martin sheen among antinuclear protesters cited at nevada test site las vegas sun  retrieved april     rep rohrabacher ‘i hope it’s your families that suffer’ from a terrorist attack think progresscom  archived from the original on  april  retrieved april     col ann wright in jail war is a crime retrieved  november    video on youtube  cbc news – us peace activists barred from entry into canadapermanent dead link  a b gorham beth  october  us antiwar activists denounce refusal at border winnipeg free press retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   gorham beth  october  prohibiting peace protesters sets dangerous precedent lethbridge herald retrieved  november