bout  yards away from the marmara wright was one of five activists who offered themselves up for arrest in rep brad shermans office after he made a public statement that any american who provides humanitarian aid to gaza should be prosecuted under the antiterrorism and effective death penalty act of  no arrests were made september th attacks and the  commission reportedit in a  interview on the air america radio network wright described the  commission report on the september  terrorist attacks as totally inadequate adding that she does not understand why the us national intelligence and defense operations completely failed and how the pentagon could be hit on  earlier in  she had signed a letter to congress criticizing the commission report for serious shortcomings and omissions which according to the signatories renders the report flawed and casts doubt on the validity of its recommendations writingsedit in  koa books published dissent voices of conscience coauthored by ann wright and susan dixon subtitled government insiders speak out against the war in iraq the work includes a forward by longtime antiwar activist daniel ellsberg who leaked the topsecret pentagon papers in  quotesedit “refusing to participate in military operations that violate international law  the war of aggression the use of torture the use of illegal weapons and purposeful targeting of innocent civilians will save lt watada his sanity and his soul” see alsoedit biography portal united states army portal first lieutenant ehren watada  former active duty united states army officer who is also against the iraq war referencesedit  nation conversations ret col ann wright on israels raid the nation june   retrieved june     rushworth katherine  october  the truth for to tell syracuse post standard retrieved  november  – via newspaper archive subscription required help   a b c mehren elizabeth  january  shes on activist duty now los angeles times retrieved  november    tehranian majid clements kevi